# SVG Icon Conventions

Icons live in `src/components/icons/` with barrel export in `index.ts`. Uses `react-native-svg`.

## Standard Icon Props

Every icon accepts `{ size?: number; color?: string }` via the shared `IconProps` type from `./types.ts`.

```tsx
import Svg, { Path } from "react-native-svg"
import type { IconProps } from "./types"

export function ExampleIcon({ size = 16, color = "currentColor", ...props }: IconProps) {
  return (
    <Svg width={size} height={size} viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" {...props}>
      <Path d="..." fill={color} />
    </Svg>
  )
}
```

## Converting SVGs with @svgr/cli (Preferred Method)

Use `@svgr/cli` to automate conversion. It handles JSX camelCase renaming, React Native SVG imports, and TypeScript output.

### One-time setup

Install as a dev dependency (already installed if present in `package.json`):

```sh
npm install --save-dev @svgr/cli
```

Create a `.svgrrc.js` config at the project root to encode all project conventions:

```js
// .svgrrc.js
module.exports = {
  native: true, // use react-native-svg imports
  typescript: true, // generate .tsx files
  expandProps: "end", // spread ...props on root <Svg>
  svgo: true, // optimize SVG with SVGO
  prettier: true, // format output
  template: require("./svgr-template.js"),
}
```

Create a custom template `svgr-template.js` at the project root to match the project's `IconProps` pattern:

```js
// svgr-template.js
const template = (variables, { tpl }) => {
  return tpl`
import type { IconProps } from "./types"

export function ${variables.componentName}({ size = 16, color = "currentColor", ...props }: IconProps) {
  return (
    ${variables.jsx}
  )
}
`
}
module.exports = template
```

### Convert a single SVG file

```sh
# Output to stdout (preview)
npx @svgr/cli --native --typescript -- icons/my-icon.svg

# Output to a specific file
npx @svgr/cli --native --typescript -- icons/my-icon.svg > src/components/icons/MyIcon.tsx

# Using the project .svgrrc.js config
npx @svgr/cli -- icons/my-icon.svg > src/components/icons/MyIcon.tsx
```

### Convert a whole directory

```sh
# Convert all SVGs in a folder, output to icons directory
npx @svgr/cli --out-dir src/components/icons -- icons/

# Skip already-existing files (safe re-run)
npx @svgr/cli --out-dir src/components/icons --ignore-existing -- icons/
```

### Key CLI options

| Option                                      | Purpose                                                                           |
| ------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `--native`                                  | Use `react-native-svg` imports (required)                                         |
| `--typescript`                              | Generate `.tsx` with TypeScript                                                   |
| `--no-dimensions`                           | Remove `width`/`height` from root SVG (use when controlling size via `size` prop) |
| `--expand-props end`                        | Spread `...props` at end of root SVG props                                        |
| `--replace-attr-values "#000=currentColor"` | Replace hardcoded fill colors with `currentColor`                                 |
| `--out-dir <dir>`                           | Output all files into a directory                                                 |
| `--ignore-existing`                         | Skip files that already exist in `--out-dir`                                      |
| `--no-index`                                | Disable auto-generated `index.js`                                                 |
| `--template <file>`                         | Use a custom component template                                                   |
| `--index-template <file>`                   | Use a custom index template                                                       |
| `--filename-case pascal`                    | PascalCase output filenames (default)                                             |
| `--ext tsx`                                 | Use `.tsx` extension                                                              |

### Recommended one-liner for a single Figma export

```sh
npx @svgr/cli --native --typescript --no-dimensions --expand-props end \
  --replace-attr-values "#000={props.color}" \
  -- path/to/figma-export.svg > src/components/icons/MyIcon.tsx
```

## Post-generation Manual Fixes

After running SVGR, review the generated file for these project-specific adjustments:

1. **Import** â€” ensure the import is `import type { IconProps } from "./types"` (not a generated SvgProps type)
2. **Props signature** â€” change to `({ size = 16, color = "currentColor", ...props }: IconProps)` if the template didn't handle it
3. **Color** â€” replace any remaining hardcoded `fill="#XXXXXX"` / `stroke="#XXXXXX"` on shape elements with `{color}`. Keep `fill="white"` on clip-path rects and `fill="none"` on the root `<Svg>`
4. **Size** â€” ensure `width={size} height={size}` on root `<Svg>` (SVGR `--no-dimensions` removes them; add back with the prop)
5. **ClipPath IDs** â€” SVGR's SVGO prefixes IDs automatically, but replace any verbose generated IDs (e.g. `clip0_14508_8231`) with short stable IDs (e.g. `search_clip`) to avoid collisions
6. **Path data** â€” NEVER simplify, round, or rewrite path coordinates â€” even small changes break `evenodd` fill rules and produce filled blobs instead of outlines
7. **Barrel export** â€” add the new icon to `src/components/icons/index.ts`

## Manual Conversion (Fallback)

If SVGR is not available or the SVG is too complex, convert manually:

1. **Path data** â€” copy the `d` attribute **exactly** from the source SVG
2. **Attributes** â€” rename HTML attrs to JSX camelCase: `fill-rule` â†’ `fillRule`, `clip-rule` â†’ `clipRule`, `clip-path` â†’ `clipPath`, `stroke-width` â†’ `strokeWidth`, `stroke-linecap` â†’ `strokeLinecap`, `stroke-linejoin` â†’ `strokeLinejoin`
3. **Color** â€” replace hardcoded `fill="#XXXXXX"` / `stroke="#XXXXXX"` on shape elements with `{color}`. Keep `fill="white"` on clip-path rects and `fill="none"` on the root `<Svg>`
4. **Size** â€” replace fixed `width`/`height` on root `<svg>` with `{size}`. Keep the original `viewBox`
5. **ClipPath IDs** â€” replace Figma-generated IDs with short stable IDs (e.g. `search_clip`)
6. **Spread rest props** â€” always spread `...props` on the root `<Svg>`
7. **Barrel export** â€” add the new icon to `src/components/icons/index.ts`
